description.narrative: The programme seeks to ensure that women are able to safely plan their pregnancies and improve their sexual and reproductive health, particularly the young and marginalized; through the following components: - Challenge social norms, increasing the demand and uptake for family planning - Provide targeted service delivery for voluntary family planning integrated within a wider sexual and reproductive health and rights package - Promote a supportive legal, financial and policy framework for sustainable family planning and safe abortion services - Leverage domestic financing and commitments for family planning and sexual and reproductive health services
